\par His question concerning the time would have been commonplace had there not been clocks facing the plaza, and disagreeing in their separate computations by no more than three minutes.
\par Marvin answered the man with his usual unfailing politness, glancing at his ankle watch and announcing the time as just five past the hour.
\par 'Thank you, sir, you are most obliging,' the man said. 'Five past already? Time devours our feeble mortality, leaving us with but the sour residue of memory.'
