Through the tortuous lanes of the central city they went, past the grim iron-g
rey walls of the Terc Fortress, past the infamous Spodney Asylum, wherein the screams of abused madmen mingled strangely with the squeak of the great waterwheel at Battlegrave Landing; past the howling of prisoners in the squat and ominous Donjon of the M
oon, and then past the malodorous High Battlement with its grisly row of spiked torsos.
